track.description: <p>Gerundino Fernández negra 1987 flamenco guitar. As a tribute to Rafael Cortés free Tabs can be downloaded on our site https://www.lasonanta.eu/en/guitarras-flamencas/gerundino-fernandez-flamenco-guitar-1987.html The more subscribers we get, the more Free Flamenco guitar lessons and Free Tabs we will publish. To subscribe to our Free Flamenco Guitar Lessons, please go to https://www.lasonanta.eu/en/la-sonanta-mailing-list If you want to know and feel how this Gerundino looks and sounds like, we invite you to watch and enjoy the included Free Flamenco guitar video lesson by our maestro Rezar Dominguez. This Free Flamenco guitar lesson consists of an intro enabling you to feel the sound and playability of this Gerundino, as well as a beautiful tremelo of Del Hoy al Ayer from Rafael Cortés. The late 'el maestro guitarrero Gerundino Fernández Garcia' (1931-2006) was, perhaps, the finest luthier of all time of the latter half of the twentieth century, along with Arcangel Fernandez and Manuel Reyes. In 1978 and 1988 he was rewarded with his mastery in the art of guitar construction, first Premio IV Concurso Internacional de Maestros Guitarreros, diploma y medalla de la UNESCO, Paris. His guitars are known for their raspy growl and volume, well balanced intonation and "gutsy" percussive sound. Gerundino's bracing system and construction maintain the essence of the true flamenco sound. Players of his instruments include Paco Peña, Paco de Lucia, Tomatito and Eric Clapton. Clapton's 1976 Gerundino sold for $16,730 at his 2004 Christie's auction, believed to be the highest price ever paid for a Gerundino. If you want to know and feel how this Gerundino looks like, we invite you to watch and enjoy the included high definition video below. You also can watch, listen and enjoy the Gerundino 2000 high definition video of our La Sonanta song played together with palmas and cajon on the detailed pages of our Gerundino blanca 2000. This 1987 Gerundino negra, made together with his old mate gonzalez, is made of master grade woods. She has a fast response and a big, woody, traditional flamenco sound. The tone is clear and focused with a slightly dark, Andalusian texture, meaning beautiful, rich, full and soulful like one expects from a really good Gerundino. She has been very well cared for, absolutely no cracks or repairs, in extremely good condition with an excellent flamenco sound. The neck is very slim and extremely comfortable to play, about 20mm deep at the first fret, the action at the tenth fret is 2mm, the distance between the strings and the soundboard at the bridge is about 8mm. This is an absolutely beautiful Gerundino, made when he was still building every one himself. Gorgeous Brazilian Rosewood. Gerundino his guitars are hard to find these days. Truly a wonderful, rare concert guitar for the serious flamenco player and collector. More information: http://www.lasonanta.eu/guitarras-flamencas/gerundino-fernandez-flamenco-guitar-1987.html</p>
